External knowledge: 
- Anomalies and changepoints are critical indicators of device performance, potentially impacting the overall efficiency and reliability of the system;
- The hierarchy of devices is based on their physical or logical installation location, which can affect how anomalies and changepoints are identified and addressed.

- Critical issues are determined by the number of anomalies and changepoints a device has, with higher numbers indicating more critical issues; 
- Devices are ranked based on the count of anomalies and changepoints in descending order; 
- The query only considers active devices.
